I'm sorry for the radio silence. My work on the latest batch of Doctor Who Icons has been delayed for a while, though they should be up before the weekend. For now, I'd like to know what you would like to see more of in this community, hence some polls for you. The first is more general, the second and third are more specific, but that should be fairly self-explanatory. As the polls say, feel free to leave your opinions in comments to this post, too. Now for the announcement. Considering the new "features" (namely the Facebook/Twitter crosspost and crosscomment) LJ has rolled out recently, the stupendously bad customer service, staff trolling users and deleting comments, I have largely migrated to Dreamwidth, which has been a very enjoyable experience so far (though I will continue maintaining this community here at LJ, too). If any of you have journals over there and want to keep following the community, you can find it at september_icons. If any of you want to migrate, please leave a comment, and I will be happy to provide you with an invite code. And that is that for today, see you around!

Another art icon post. ^^ I had originally intended (and will do that, at some later point) to make an art post featuring Tolkien's own art, Alan Lee, John Howe, and Ted Nasmith. Googling them brought up an artist I hadn't heard of previously, namely, Jeff Murray. While he is not necessarily focused on realism, I really enjoyed his take on Tolkien's world, especially his vibrant use of colour is gorgeous, and definitely bears looking at in full view: Jeff Murray's Gallery featuring Silmarillion, Hobbit and LotR art. Crossposted to . When I mentioned Neil Gaiman quotes posting my latest batch of NaNo icons, the lovely was kind enough to post another very inspirational quote. Why write? The best thing about writing fiction is that moment where the story catches fire and comes to life on the page, and suddenly it all makes sense and you know what it's about and why you're doing it and what these people are saying and doing, and you get to feel like both the creator and the audience. Everything is suddenly both obvious and surprising ("but of course that's why he was doing that, and that means that...") and it's magic and wonderful and strange. You don't live there always when you write. Mostly it's a long hard walk. Sometimes it's a trudge through fog and you're scared you've lost your way and can't remember why you set out in the first place. But sometimes you fly, and that pays for everything. -- The Journal, 10/15/07 It does ring true, and is very motivational and inspirational on top of it... and what could be better than such a quote right before your eyes every time you sit glaring at your computer during those long tedious weeks of NaNo, or when another writer's block hits? Therefore, wallpapers.

Because I am still behind - after temporarily giving up - I decided to read and re-read the pep talks from NaNoWriMo 2007 and 2008, plus some Neil Gaiman quotes - he never fails to inspire me, and is on a close second place of my favourite authors together with Naomi Novik, both coming just behind Tolkien. It worked this time. I'm writing - well, not right now, obviously, but managed to catch up a little and it's going well despite a stomach bug that is making things difficult. -_- Aaaaanyway, more icons! Sorry. If you really want to know, feel free to ask, I'll try to find out. Let me just say that if I were a citizen of the United States, Senator Obama would have both my voice and my vote. I'm on the other side of the Atlantic Ocean, but his speeches have not failed to inspire me, his ideas have not failed to impress me, and his philosophy has not failed to move me. We are the ones we have been waiting for, indeed. I am - and have been for a long while - sceptical about the self-appointed idea of the United States being this world's only possible savior and/or salvation, but I believe that Senator Obama, if he gets elected, can be a great leader and great example to spark movements that may bring about the changeS that are needed. Please, don't f*ck this up. Feel free to distribute, share, link (not hotlink), modify, whathaveyou. Spread the word.
